cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.NE, cs.SD 

The paper deals with a vision problem of detecting objects in physics-based experiments, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The approach proposed in the paper involves unsupervised iterative clustering-based segmentation, which can also be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The use of statistical analysis and hyper-parameter tuning can be associated with neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SD) categories.
